<subSubSection id="128274369AAFC8C63B169D86F31B20A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="178F928C278BE838196DA0E083F54644" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49989C709B84FA9A28682FFA6E111556" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
MEXICO. 
<normalizedToken id="B82A82BADC1A14AE737233495F643574" originalValue="Querétaro">Queretaro</normalizedToken>
, Hac. Ciervo, 
<emphasis id="7965115F471F5C26BCC566604CFFEDE9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rose &amp; Painter</emphasis>
9660 (holotype US00036708, isotypes MEXU00025165, NY00319080).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FB663FA6D8326531ECCF8AF77768D9C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="4709C2BB513ACFCEA8FB34BA079BDC7A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39A6481FE084BE76259E82D145CECC26" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Erect perennial subshrub to 80 cm from a tuberous rootstock, stem densely tomentose, often much branched from base. Leaves imbricate, shortly petiolate, 4-10 
<normalizedToken id="42EBC2034F9C4AFEC45C039BC66EC080" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-5 cm, elliptic, apex acute or obtuse, base cuneate, densely white-tomentose on both surfaces but paler beneath; petioles 3-5 mm. Inflorescence of solitary axillary flowers; peduncles 1.5-2 cm, densely pubescent; bracteoles 14-16 mm long, linear spathulate, tomentose; pedicels 4-9 mm; sepals subequal, 15-23 mm, lanceolate, attenuate, white-tomentose; corolla 4.5-6 cm long, funnel-shaped, white, pubescent, limb entire to undulate. Capsules 8-10 
<normalizedToken id="0EB33EEED92F806A180F8D04DE5A97FD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 mm, conical, glabrous; seeds glabrous except for white marginal hairs c. 3 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
